  "name": "A F M Moniruzzaman Shipu",
  "title": "Assistant Professor",
  "department": "School of Social Science",
  "school": "",
  "profile_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/faculty/a-f-m-moniruzzaman-shipu",
  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/Moniruzzaman.jpg?itok=6LiNvSiA",
  "bio_raw": "He has been teaching Media Studies at the University of Liberal Arts since 2014.\nHe has six years experience in training and producing Animation at one of Bangladesh’s most prestigious animation studios, TOONBANGLA, from 2008-2014.\nSince 1999 he has also been involved in fine art shows and participated in several art exhibitions and festivals.\nCreative Works:\n‘Migration’ (Interactive Graffiti in 2014), ‘Apon’s Bike (15 min Short Animation Film produced in Japan in 2006), ‘Shadows of Dhaka City’ (Solo painting & printmaking exhibition in 1999), ‘Green Man in Self Jail’ (Performance Art in 1995),",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Painting, Printmaking, Animation, Film"
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMaster in Fine Art (Printmaking)\nMaster in Film Making (Animation)"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nChapters:  ‘Animation’, ‘Cinema Studies & Training,’ published by Bangladesh Cinema and Television Institute, Dhaka in 2016.\nDate: 01/01/2016\nGrabbing a new place in painting\nAuthors: Jang S Verman &\nA.F.M. Moniruzzaman\nPublishers: Daily Earth News (Art & Culture).\nDate: 01/19/2020",
    "Conference Proceedings\nShadows of Cuttack City-2(Acrylic on Canvas)\nInternational Painting Symposium, Department of Visual & Performing Arts at Sri Sri University, India.\nDate: 01/22/2020\nSri Sir Ravi Shankar-2(Acrylic on Canvas)\nInternational Painting Symposium, Department of Visual & Performing Arts at Sri Sri University, India.\nDate: 01/22/2020\nJury, 9th Bangla Olympiad Competition, International Hope School, Bangladesh, Main Campus, International Hope School, Uttara, Dhaka, Bangladesh\nDate: 02/29/2020",
    "Works\nVisiting Faculty, Department of Animation & New Media, Sri Sri University, Sri Sri University, Odisha India\nDate: 01/14/2020\nJury of Graffiti Art Competition , Department Architecture, Sri Sri University, Sri Sri University, Odisha India.\nDate: 01/17/2020\nJury of Painting competition of 9th Bangla Olympiad Competition, International Hope School, Bangladesh, Main Campus, International Hope School, Uttara, Dhaka, Bangladesh\nDate: 02/29/2020"
